{"ts":"2026-07-19T03:43:10.112Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"append","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"GH-607. A structurally-unparseable item .toon (e.g. count header disagreeing with data lines — exactly what a botched concurrent-append merge produces, pm-9q2t) is silently skipped by pm validate: ok:true, checked_items:0, while pm get on the same item exits 1 \"TOON item document is not valid TOON\". The workspace-integrity command must fail on provably unreadable items; checked_items vs on-disk file-count mismatch is itself a failure. Related counts-only precedent pm-a9mc."},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-19T03:43:10.112Z"}],"before_hash":"f93f76bab479b70d468e423e3abd8d4956ad951b5b57bb62f90175de892e2133","after_hash":"ca0aee4232f5a18187bcab654d4ba68d963b6a8aec62a1144224a51152e30a83"}
